    "body": "## Problem\n\n## Steps to reproduce\n\n`nvim --clean repro.lua`, `:so<cr>`\n```lua\nvim.o.cursorline = true\nvim.cmd([[au TermOpen * startinsert]])\nvim.cmd.enew()\nvim.cmd.term(\"/bin/sh\")\nvim.wo[0][0].cursorline = false\n-- vim.api.nvim_buf_delete(0, { force = true })\nvim.defer_fn(function()\n\tvim.api.nvim_buf_delete(0, { force = true })\nend, 100)\nvim.defer_fn(function() assert(vim.o.cursorline) end, 200)\n```\n\n## Expected behavior\n`cursorline` should be enabled in the original buffer at the end.\n\n## System info\n\n- Nvim version (nvim -v): `v0.12.0-dev-2076 g103ddaf9ae-dirty` neovim/neovim@103ddaf9ae\n- Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?: ?\n- Operating system/version: Linux 6.18.5-zen1-1-zen\n- Terminal name/version: kitty\n- $TERM environment variable: `xterm-kitty`\n- Installation: ?\n\n",
